\end{align*}
From the first equation, we get $3r = -6$, which means $r = -2$. Now, substituting the value of $r$ into the second equation, we get:
\begin{align*}
2(-2) \cdot (-2) &= k \\
8 &= k
\end{align*}
So, the value of $k$ is $\boxed{8}$.
